NEWS

* You can now easily grow a stack of partition, encrypted volume and filesystem.

* Simple flatpak management is now possible with an mcl class.

* The exec resource grew an ifequals param. This takes even more bash out of the
equation when writing mcl code.

* A new gsettings resource makes management of GNOME settings (and more) very
easy.

* We added nifcmd, nifcwd, and nifshell params to the exec resource.

* A regression in the virt-builder resource was fixed.

* Karpfen improved our func generation for golang 1.25 which helps out the nix
people.

* We added an fwattr resource to manage BIOS settings via the linux
firmware-attributes API.

* SSH world reconnections now work properly and have backoff.

* We now automatically raise inotify limits at startup. This shouldn't hurt
anyone but if you've got a reason you're affected negatively, please let us know
why.

* The user resource wasn't setting all the group things correctly. This is now
fixed. Thanks to user "thijs" for the report.

* We're looking for help writing Amazon, Google, DigitalOcean, Hetzner, etc,
resources if anyone is interested, reach out to us. Particularly if there is
support from those organizations as well.

* Many other bug fixes, changes, etc...

* See the git log for more NEWS, and for anything notable I left out!


BUGS/TODO

* Function values getting _passed_ to resources doesn't work yet, but it's not a
blocker, but it would definitely be useful. We're looking into it.

* We don't have any aarch64 hardware, so no more arm64 builds or testing until
we get a donation or sponsor for that unfortunately.

* We don't have the <|> operator merged yet. Expect that when we do this, we'll
consider removing the || (default) operator. This is the only pending language
change that I know of, and these cases are easily caught by the compiler and can
be easily patched.

* Autoedge performance isn't great. It can easily be disabled. Most of the time
I just specify my edges, so this is really a convenience feature, but it should
be looked into when we have a chance.


